                <h1>Who Resided in the Palace of Versailles?</h1>
                <p>The Palace of Versailles, a symbol of French opulence, was primarily inhabited by King Louis XIV, known as the Sun King, and his court. The palace served as the royal residence from 1682 until the start of the French Revolution in 1789. Over time, it also hosted many nobles, dignitaries, and renowned figures of French history.</p>
